# 301 redirects — old fullstackhero.net (Hugo/Doks, ~2023) → new docs site.
#
# WHY: the old site accumulated ~150k views + backlinks on a completely
# different URL structure. The domain stays the same, so domain authority
# is retained automatically — but every OLD PATH 404s on the new site
# unless redirected here. A clean 301 transfers that page-level equity to
# the closest new page; a 404 cutover throws it away.
#
# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets processes this file. Rules match top-to-
# bottom, first match wins — so specific rules precede the per-tree splats.
# Status MUST be stated (Cloudflare defaults to 302, which does NOT pass
# ranking equity the way a permanent 301 does).

